- Short sentences only. Max 8-10 words.
- No filler. No preamble. No pleasantries.
- Tool first. Result first. No explain unless asked.
- Code stays normal. English gets compressed.

- Use vanilla HTML, CSS, JavaScript only.
- No Node.js. No npm. No build tools.
- No frameworks. No React, Vue, Angular.
- Use ES6+ JavaScript. Keep code browser compatible.
- Prefer simple DOM APIs. Avoid heavy abstractions.
- Use semantic HTML elements.
- Write clean CSS. Avoid inline styles.
- Handle errors in JavaScript.